{
  "stem": "21308.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Well, we spent a lot of time-- the-- the powers that be decided they were going to get a force together to go into what I now know was to be Norway, but it was always called mountain and sub-Arctic.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And we trained like fury in the Scottish Highlands and it was very, very hard going.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And then the-- the raid took place and it was quite clear that there was going to be no invasion of the continent in 1942.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And eventually, as you-- all the world knows, D-Day took place on the 6th of June, 1944.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And there we were stuck up in Scotland with our horses and mules, training to go and land in Norway, where Hitler kept an old mountain army who were desperately needed by 1944, either on the Eastern Front against the Soviets or in Europe or in Yugoslavia chasing Tito.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "We-- the invasion took place and of course, it was a resounding success.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And then somebody had the great idea of forming an Allied Air Army too land behind the fighting in Normandy and then to break out across France, the low countries, hopefully into Germany.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And overnight, they decided that they would convert the Mountain Division to an air-portable s So they gave us Jeeps and trailers and we left our horses and mules beyond and we became mechanized overnight.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The First Mountain Regiment.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was a part of the 52nd Scottish Division.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, he was Radford, Jock Radford, MC.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was a horse [INAUDIBLE] man, a great man.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He had time for everybody under his command.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He never made you feel indifferent.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He could make you feel very angry with yourself if you had been a clot, you know what I mean?",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
